# SCSS Fallback and Token Governance

- ONLY use SCSS when Tailwind becomes unmanageable, requires complex pseudo-element orchestration, or for legacy/third-party overrides where Tailwind cannot be applied.
- When SCSS is required, ALWAYS use CSS Modules with `[name].module.scss` for local scoping.
- ALWAYS use `.scss` block syntax. NEVER use indented `.sass` syntax.
- Restrict global SCSS files to resets (if not covered by preflight), global CSS custom properties, and `@font-face` declarations.
- NEVER put component-specific classes or DOM element styling in global SCSS files.
- NEVER use `@import`; ALWAYS use `@use` for variables, mixins, and functions.
- Group shared configuration into partials and expose via a central `@forward` entry point so local modules can consume with one `@use`.
- NEVER hardcode hex, `rgb/rgba`, or named colors in SCSS or inline styles.
- In SCSS, map all values to globally defined design system tokens (`@use` variables or CSS custom properties).
- Check the existing global palette/token set before introducing any new token.
